Simple Logging Facade for Java

https://www.slf4j.org/manual.html

1. Add log4j APIs -> log4j-api and core in Maven
2. Add log4j-slf4j-impl in maven to use SLF4j with log4j

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.apache.logging.log4j</groupId>
    <artifactId>log4j-api</artifactId>
    <version>2.7</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.apache.logging.log4j</groupId>
    <artifactId>log4j-core</artifactId>
    <version>2.7</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.apache.logging.log4j</groupId>
    <artifactId>log4j-slf4j-impl</artifactId>
    <version>2.7</version>
</dependency>

3. Find the latest version in maven repositary

ERROR StatusLogger No log4j2 configuration file found. Using default configuration: logging only errors to the console.
4. Add the Log4j configuration file in resource folder and add it as class path folder